## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 2 (systemic — affecting all 10 tests) |
| **Medium** | 1 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. All 10 public methods of `ProductCatalog` are called — achieving high line-coverage — but virtually nothing is verified. These tests will pass even if every method is silently broken.

---

### 🔴 Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (systemic — all 10 tests)

The class methodically calls every method on `ProductCatalog` without asserting meaningful outcomes. The pattern is unmistakable: one test per public method, named `*_Works`, either zero assertions or a trivial `IsNotNull`.

**6 of 10 tests have zero assertions:**

| Test | What's unverified |
|------|-------------------|
| `AddProduct_Works` (L17) | Product was actually stored |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33) | Price actually changed from 9.99 → 14.99 |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` (L39) | Product was actually deleted |
| `GetProductCount_Works` (L63) | Count value (doesn't even capture the return) |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L69) | Prices were reduced by 10% |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L85) | Any products were created from CSV |

**Concrete fix — `ApplyBulkDiscount` (worst offender, hides math bugs):**

```csharp
// BEFORE — passes even if discount is applied backwards
[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_Works()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 19.99m));
    _catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
}

// AFTER — verifies the 10% reduction
[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_ReducesPricesByFraction()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 10.00m));
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 20.00m));

    _catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);

    Assert.AreEqual(9.00m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
    Assert.AreEqual(18.00m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")!.Price);
}
```

**Concrete fix — `RemoveProduct`:**

```csharp
// BEFORE
[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_Works()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
